GUANGZHOU, Oct. 30 (Xinhua) -- China's top epidemiologist Zhong Nanshan said that the country will be able to effectively contain the latest COVID-19 resurgence within a month. Zhong made the remarks during a webinar attended by medical professionals on Saturday, as sporadic local COVID-19 cases have been reported in various parts of the country. "The coronavirus and the pandemic cannot be eradicated within a short period of time," said Zhong, calling on other countries to adopt strict and prioritized measures against COVID-19 and actively roll out vaccination. Zhong said he expects that more than 80 percent of Chinese residents will have been fully vaccinated by the end of this year. Enditem